OL,3,CLady Donaldson tells trial of 'blank
OL,4,Cwall' from husband over incident
OL,6,FHe said that a letter he had written
OL,7,Fto Complainant A was not an apology
OL,8,Ffor sex abuse.
OL,10,FThe trial previously heard that in
OL,11,F2020, Donaldson wrote to Complainant A
OL,12,Fexpressing "regret" for the "hurt,
OL,13,Fpain and distress" he had caused her.
OL,15,FIn her evidence, the woman said she
OL,16,Fthought the letter was an attempt to
OL,17,F"apologise" for the alleged abuse.
OL,19,FHe told police: "None of that is to do
OL,20,Fwith any allegation or any action
OL,21,Finvolving sexual abuse."
